Posted: December 22, 2015
Early Access Review
								I love this game.  It has the potential to be everything I am looking for in this type of game.  Of course, it is fairly bare bones at this time.  It needs a ton more content, crafting recipes, heroes, etc.  But it is relaxing, pretty, and well-made for the current stage.Stuff I'd add:--roads that we can place ourselves;--salvaging (it's there but not functional);--more crafting recipes, MORE!!!--monsters that respawn more in Sandbox;--make villagers eat more at one time -- early game all they do is walk to the Storehouse and back, it seems, unless you keep them on point;--ability to slightly reposition buildings (rotate?);--aesthetic buildings -- roads, props, flowers, stuff like that;--more heroes that you can recruit at the Tavern;
